Implement Automated Offer Expiration
We will add a scheduled task to check for expired collocation offers and send an email notification to the offer's owner. We will ensure duplicate emails are not sent by tracking notification state in the database.

Proposed Changes
Configuration & Dependencies
[MODIFY] 
pom.xml
Add spring-boot-starter-mail dependency.
[MODIFY] 
application.properties
Add spring email configuration with Gmail SMTP and the provided credentials.
Entity & Repository Layers
[MODIFY] 
collocOffre.java
Add private Boolean notified = false; to track if the email was already sent.
[MODIFY] 
collocOffreRepo.java
Add a custom query method: List<collocOffre> findByExpiryDateBeforeAndNotifiedFalseOrNotifiedIsNull(LocalDate date);
Services & Schedulers
[NEW] EmailService.java
Create a service wrapping JavaMailSender to handle email delivery.
[NEW] UserSecurityClient.java
Create a service to fetch user details (email) using ownerId. (I will use RestTemplate or Spring Cloud Feign to mock findUserById(ownerId) assuming a standard user-service pattern).
